This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-weston-remote-distro layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

Dependencies
============
  URI: https://github.com/ronpscg/meta-weston-remote
  branch: master

  No further, dependencies, but you can follow https://github.com/ronpscg/vnc-rdp-pki-creation-for-weston to generate your own PKI materials, instead of the materials packaged in
  the meta-weston-remote repo.
  
Patches
=======

Please submit any patches against the meta-weston-remote-distro layer to the xxxx mailing list (xxxx@zzzz.org)
and cc: the maintainer:

Maintainer: Ron Munitz <ron@thepscg.com>

Table of Contents
=================

  I. Adding the meta-weston-remote-distro layer to your build
 II. Misc


I. Adding the meta-weston-remote-distro layer to your build
=================================================

Run 'bitbake-layers add-layer meta-weston-remote-distro'

To build, use:
DISTRO=simple-weston-remote-distro bitbake core-image-weston

You can alternatively start from scratch, and use:
. oe-init-build-env yourbuilddir
MACHINE=qcom-armv8a DISTRO=simple-weston-remote-distro bitbake core-image-weston


